-- Czech Stocks: Erste Group Bank, Orco Property Group Active
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-05-25T15:01:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/czech-stocks-erste-group-bank-orco-property-group-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
fell 1.1 percent to 869.6 at its close in Prague, paring weekly
gains to less than 0.01 percent.  The following were among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)   of Austria slid 1.2 percent
to 364.5 koruna, paring gains this week to 0.4 percent. The euro
touched its weakest since July 2010 versus the dollar and bank
shares were among the worst performers in Europe as concern rose
Spain’s regional governments may lose access to  capital markets .  Orco Property Group SA (ORCO)   increased 15 percent to 69
koruna, rebounding from a record low. The developer in central
 Europe  earlier rallied as much as 21 percent, the most since
2009, after saying it returned to profit in the first quarter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
